This paper deals with scheduling problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves minimizing the makespan, which is a common objective in game theory (cs.GT) and combinatorial optimization (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents an approximation algorithm, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
